# gin-restful

Flask-RESTful style REST API library for Gin. See AGENTS.md for full details.

## Quick Reference

### Resource Pattern
Implement only the interfaces you need — only those routes are registered:
- `Lister` → GET /path
- `Getter` → GET /path/:id
- `Poster` → POST /path
- `Putter` → PUT /path/:id
- `Patcher` → PATCH /path/:id
- `Deleter` → DELETE /path/:id

All methods return `(any, int, error)`.

### Request Binding
- `restful.Bind[T](c)` → returns `(*T, error)`, handle error yourself
- `restful.MustBind[T](c)` → returns `*T`, auto 400 abort on failure (check nil)

### Error Handling
- `restful.Abort(status, message)` → structured HTTP error
- Non-HTTPError errors → 500 with generic message (internal details hidden)

### Registration
```go
api := restful.NewAPI(engine, "/api/v1")
api.AddResource("/items", &ItemResource{})
```

### Rules
- Always use `sync.RWMutex` for shared state in resource structs
- Use `Abort()` for client-facing errors, never raw `fmt.Errorf`
- Run `go test ./... -v` after changes
- Package imported as `restful`
